The paper deals with the problem of computing the minimum number of flips required to transform one triangulation of a convex polygon to another, which is a problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the NP-completeness of two natural generalizations of the problem, which suggests that it may belong to sub-categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
